  {
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @Haroenv thanks for this suggestion. The alternative code isn't working for me, still shows the default list of items. (It appears `results.query` is undefined). Based on the API reference it looks like it's missing the brackets around `{ results }` in `transformItems(items, { results })`.\r\n\r\nWhen I add those, it works, but then of course it shows the same text as the empty template, as you mention, which isn't ideal. I'm able to customize that though by setting the empty template, as below. It may help to include such a suggestion in the docs for this option:\r\n```js\r\nhits({\r\n  transformItems(items, { results }) {\r\n    if (results.query === '') return [];\r\n    return items;\r\n  },\r\n  templates: {\r\n    empty(results, {html}) {\r\n      if (results.query === '') return null;\r\n      return html`No results found for \"${results.query}\"`;\r\n    },\r\n  }\r\n});\r\n```\r\n",
    "created_at": "2024-05-14T14:39:33Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6194#issuecomment-2110422266",
